quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,1,"Ta'. Sin. Mim."
  26,2,"These are the verses of the Clear Book.",footnotes:179695:1
  26,3,"(O Muhammad), you will perhaps grieve yourself to death because these people do not believe.",footnotes:179696:1
  26,4,"If We will, We can send down a Sign to them from heaven, so their necks will be humbled to it.",footnotes:179697:1
  26,5,"Never does there come to them an admonition from the Merciful Lord but they turn away from it."
  26,6,"They will soon come to know the truth of that which they have been scoffing at.",footnotes:179698:1
  26,7,"Do they not look at the earth, how We caused a variety of fine vegetation to grow from it (in abundance)?"
  26,8,"Surely there is a Sign in this, but most of them would not believe.",footnotes:179699:1,footnotes:179700:2
  26,9,"Verily Your Lord is Infinitely Mighty, Most Compassionate."
  26,10,"(Recount to them about the time) when Your Lord called Moses: "Go to the wrong-doing people,",footnotes:179701:1,footnotes:179702:2